  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse your <strong>brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1711456692032-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1711456692032-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1711456692032-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1711456692032-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1711456692032-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>coriander seeds</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, transfer the <strong>coriander seeds</strong> to a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> and crush roughly</p><p>Reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1711456695762-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1711456695762-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1711456695762-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1711456695762-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1711456695762-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>hake fillet[s]</strong> into small bite-sized pieces and pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Return the pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>hake pieces</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min, turning once half way, or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1711456699743-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1711456699743-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1711456699743-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1711456699743-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1711456699743-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the fish is cooking, boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Once cooked, transfer the<strong> hake </strong>to a plate, reduce the heat to medium-low and add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> to the pan</p><p>Cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1711456703618-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1711456703618-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1711456703618-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1711456703618-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1711456703618-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>peanut butter</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>creamed coconut</strong> in 350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[455ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1711456707669-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1711456707669-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1711456707669-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1711456707669-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1711456707669-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger</strong>, <strong>ground turmeric</strong>, <strong>cayenne pepper </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>and<strong> crushed coriander seeds</strong> to the pan and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Increase the heat to medium, add your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> and <strong>coconut stock</strong> and cook for 7-9 min or until thickened</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1711456711406-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1711456711406-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1711456711406-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1711456711406-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1711456711406-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop most of your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks (reserve some leaves for garnish!)</p><p>Add the<strong> cooked hake</strong> and <strong>chopped coriander</strong> to the sauce and cook for 1 min further – this is your <strong>Brazilian-style</strong> <strong>hake & coriander curry</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>lime[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Add the juice of <strong>half</strong> the <strong>lime</strong> <strong>wedges</strong> to the curry (save the rest for garnish!)</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1711456714844-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1711456714844-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1711456714844-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1711456714844-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1711456714844-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Brazilian-style hake<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>& coriander curry</strong> over the <strong>brown rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>reserved coriander leaves</strong> and<strong> lime wedges</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
